				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OOT:<br>   1. I found leveling from 13 - 15.5 pretty nice with the sirens. I prefer the southern rocks, with the 2 sirens on one rocks and 3 on the other. I would reiterate what people have said about the two together on the rocks with three, insofar as that they do aggro so you have to be ready to take out the first one ASAP when two come. But once you break that spawn it is a nice almost constant circuit between the five sirens (and the two goblins if you want). Only downside is there is almost no gold (which was a concern with those L16 spell costs). But more on money below.<br>   2. For those who don't remember, the above set of rocks are the ones when you take the boat FROM Butcherblock. Basically the first landmark in the OOT zone. One nice thing about those rocks is that if you bind there, you can jump the boat when it comes by to the Inn if you want to sell off any items (goblin bows sell for 1.5 gold or so). Then when you're ready to head back, can take boat to Antonica, or take a canoe from inn island up to northern siren rocks, and grab the boat from there back to butcherblock. Or to return to Fay continent take the boat from 5 siren rocks and just go all the way to Freeport and back.<br>   3. Other siren rocks: I did try the ones on the way out of OOT back toward Butcher. There are two on one rock, and a third on a rock with three goblins. None of these guys group aggro, which is nice. But I prefered the nice cycle of the five on the other rocks.<br>   4. Aviak island: This was a bit of a let down. At my level (L14), it took me about three hours of attempts and fails (and gates back to inn island) to find Aviak. Of course, I was trying to do it from the Inn island on the way from Butcher to Freeport. Anyhow, I finally figured out to take the canoe from that island as close as I could until the canoe travel wouldn't go any further, then swim the remainder 2000 or so coords. Anyhow, the island was a bit of a let down. Sure, there is a nice range of Aviaks (blue, white, yellow), but I often had to wait for one to come low enough on the beach to pull. I died twice there when a couple would come from over the ridge, higher than I thought their aggro range was, and it was a pain to then get back and get my corpse. The money side is a little better though, with aviak horns selling for about 5 gold.<br><br>Wisps and money:<br>   1. OK, while the sirens were good and interesting hunting -- both in terms of xp and practicing tactics with pet for pulling two at a time -- it was horrible for money. I mean, I'm looking at maybe having made 5 plats in 2.5 levels of xp. And those L16 spells and their prices (shudder). And keep in mind this is a non-twink GnoMage. The contrast was especially bad because gnomes have it so easy from L1-L12 because Steamfont is so lucrative in terms of plats.<br>   2. OK, so like many I zeroed in on Wisps. At L12, this was actually pretty great since fire pets solo them pretty easily, and I get solid blue xp through at least L13. So in probably 6 hours of hunting in East Commons (the flats near the guard/toll booth) I got about 7-9 great and 10-15 normal lightstones. Normal lightstones, 5 gold each. Not bad. BUT, I didn't cash in the greaters. No, I hitched a port to nexus, took the spire down to north karana, and gave them to the gypsy (myrlia ro something like that). And voila, research books that sell for 7.5 plat! So each greater in the end could sell for 7.5 plat. Now THAT helped me out financially. If you do that trick, just be careful to have your pet out because lions and wolves go through the gypsy camp constantly. And of course if you're evil align, you'll want to do the same thing but with the Dark Elf vendor is S.Ro.<br><br>Whew. OK, I know that was kinda long, but I appreciated some of the info when I was L12 and looking to hunt, so wanted to pass my experiences along.<br><br>Now I'm onto the L16-19 trek...<br><br><br>Arcani<br>L16 GnoMage<br>Fennin Ro<br><br>   2. The above Siren spot is also nice because the boat from Butcher to <br>   2. Aviak  <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
