				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I went to Erud's Crossing at lvl 8 for Wisps, and was successful as long as I just pulled 1 wisp.  Like you said, any add was death.<br><br>After getting sick of the boat ride back, I found a new strategy.  Chain casting pets.<br><br>Using Water for their overall stats and non-wasted shock spell, I would pull as usual (never without fm, though).  IF another wisp added, I had a strategy that did not involve gateing back to Qeynos.  First, summon about 4 staffs or daggers.  They do make a difference!  When the pet gets below 40%, give yourself some room and start casting the pet WITH the inventory window open.  With one bubble of casting time left, click &quot;GO AWAY&quot; and your nearly dead pet will suicide, just in time for your new one to appear.  Quickly give it a staff or dagger.  By this time the wisps are on you, and he will draw them off.  Repeat until the wisps are dead, you run out of malachite, or run out of mana.  The last two are certain death, btw.<br><br>I never had more than 1 add, but I had enough mana for gate just in case.<br><br>The money is unbeatable.  I had plenty for all my lvl 12 spells, and walked away several levels higher. <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
